                               In this issue...

     It is with great sadness I learned from Carol and Brenda late
     Tuesday night, that Doug Myers, Editor of FidoNews passed away last
     week.  This is a "Shortie" to fill in for that missing Fido News
     Letter.  I am sure many more would like to have their personal
     eulogies included, but time is of the essence. Any eulogies for
     Doug will be included in the next Fidonews letter.  I felt a great
     loss for Fidonet, and wanted all to know we have lost a very bright
     light in Fido; a light that always tried to illuminate the positive
     and draw peoples of the whole earth, all zones, together in warm
     fun and friendship.

     Doug was deeper than he pretended to be in his humor, and his
     intelligence showed through, "in every pixel on the monitor
     screen!", (courtesy Brenda in a phone conversation early this am).
     I could not have said it better.  I will miss that wonderful sense
     of humor he lavishly inserted in his "one liner" replies. Doug was
     a fair minded editor, about all matters brought to his attention.
     He analyzed everything in a logical light, prepared his comments in
     a way that pulled our hearts and minds above the thorns of
     complaint and conflict,  to smell the sweetness of the roses,
     which are our friendships on this FidoNet world wide web.

     Goodbye to a dear, dear friend.
     Ol'WDB
     ~~~~~~~~~~
     Add me to the above sentiments! I'm sure the position of Fidonews
     Editor will be filled, but the shoes of Doug Myers will not.  Words
     that come to mind are, friend to all, compassion, caring,
     understanding and a million more such.... all totally inadequate in
     their description of Doug.

     Best regards to all,
     Frank  Vest - N124C
